            "name": "backstory",
            "value": "Megan Riley\u2019s story is one of pragmatic ambition, rooted in the sun-baked suburbs of Modesto. Growing up in a practical, blue-collar family, she learned early on that passion needed a business plan. While her friends played with dolls, Megan was giving them intricate braids and experimental haircuts, her first sign of a natural talent. Her parents encouraged her, but with a caveat: \u201cArt is great, honey, but you need to know how to run a business.\u201d\n\nShe took their advice to heart, enrolling in a community college program that allowed her to simultaneously pursue a cosmetologist license and take business administration classes. It was a grueling schedule, but Megan was focused. She saw the two paths not as separate, but as intertwined necessities for the future she envisioned.\n\nAt 23, drawn by the city\u2019s vibrant culture and professional opportunities, Megan moved to San Francisco. She started by renting a chair in a busy Union Square salon, where she spent years honing her craft, building a fiercely loyal client base who valued her technical skill and her ability to truly listen. It was there she met Sofia, another stylist with a complementary aesthetic and a shared dream.\n\nThe turning point came at age 32. After a long-term relationship ended, Megan poured her energy and savings into a new partnership with Sofia. They took a terrifying leap, securing a small business loan and signing a lease on a space in Hayes Valley. This venture, their co-owned salon, became her life\u2019s work. Her business classes proved invaluable in navigating permits, payroll, and marketing.\n\nToday, Megan\u2019s life is woven into the fabric of her neighborhood. Her 0.8-mile walk to the salon is a daily ritual, often including a stop for coffee at a local caf\u00e9 where the baristas know her order. Her days are a blur of consultations, cuts, and managing the business, but she thrives on the energy. Her social circle is a tight-knit group of friends and long-time clients. While she\u2019s open to a new relationship, her priority is nurturing the life and business she built from scratch. Her dream is no longer just about survival, but about legacy: mentoring new stylists and ensuring her salon remains a cornerstone of the community she proudly calls home."
